label: Pubic symphysis morphological stage value specification
editor preferred term: Hartnett pubic symphysis morphological stage value specification
definition: A categorical value specification for pubic symphysis morphology ratings according to Hartnett (2010).
definition source: Hartnett, K. M. (2010). Analysis of Age-at-Death Estimation Using Data from a New, Modern Autopsy Sample—Part I: Pubic Bone. Journal of Forensic Sciences 55(5), Table A1. doi: 10.1111/j.1556-4029.2010.01399.x
referenced category labels: ('has category label' exactly 1 ({hpa:PubicSymphysisMorphologicalStage1, hpa:PubicSymphysisMorphologicalStage2, hpa:PubicSymphysisMorphologicalStage3, hpa:PubicSymphysisMorphologicalStage4, hpa:PubicSymphysisMorphologicalStage5, hpa:PubicSymphysisMorphologicalStage6, hpa:PubicSymphysisMorphologicalStage7 }))

label: Sorting directive for a pubic symphysis morphological stage label
editor preferred term: Sorting directive for a Hartnett (2010) pubic symphysis morphological stage label
definition: A sorting specification about the position of a category label within the ordinal scale defined by a pubic symphysis morphological stage value specification.
definition source: Hartnett, K. M. (2010). Analysis of Age-at-Death Estimation Using Data from a New, Modern Autopsy Sample—Part I: Pubic Bone. Journal of Forensic Sciences 55(5), Table A1. doi: 10.1111/j.1556-4029.2010.01399.x

label: Hartnett (2010) female age range value specification
editor preferred term: Hartnett (2010) female age range value specification
definition: An age range value specification defining the female age range for one of the pubic symphysis morphological stages defined by Hartnett (2010).
definition source: Hartnett, K. M. (2010). Analysis of Age-at-Death Estimation Using Data from a New, Modern Autopsy Sample—Part I: Pubic Bone. Journal of Forensic Sciences 55(5), Table 7. doi: 10.1111/j.1556-4029.2010.01399.x

label: Female phase 1 age range value specification
definition: This value specification specifies the female age range assigned to pubic symphysis morphological stage 1 in Hartnett (2010).
definition source: Hartnett, K. M. (2010). Analysis of Age-at-Death Estimation Using Data from a New, Modern Autopsy Sample—Part I: Pubic Bone. Journal of Forensic Sciences 55(5), Table 7. doi: 10.1111/j.1556-4029.2010.01399.x
editor note: The point estimate value represents the mean value reported by Hartnett (2010, Table 7).
